&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated &lt;strong&gt;Associate Food Scientist&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Beverage team. In this role, you will support critical beverage initiatives and assist in the development of new products. Reporting to the Manager, Beverage R&amp;amp;D, you will help convert market strategies into finished concentrates used in our high-tech dispensers. From benchtop prototyping to refining formulas based on consumer feedback, you will play a hands-on role in unbottling the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day to Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Execute Formulations:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the development of new beverage formulations by performing benchtop experiments based on concepts provided by senior team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prototyping:&lt;/strong&gt; Create small-batch prototype runs in-house, ensuring accuracy in measurements and consistency in flavor profiles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lab Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the day-to-day operations of the beverage lab, including equipment maintenance, calibration, sanitation, and maintaining a meticulous inventory of ingredients and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Documentation:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain detailed and organized records of formula development, sensory feedback, and experimental results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sensory Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in organizing sensory analysis panels and product testing, collecting and consolidating data for the broader team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with the Hardware &amp;amp; Quality teams to monitor the stability of products in development, in production, and in the Bevi machine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ingredient Sourcing:&lt;/strong&gt; Help identify and source new ingredients, coordinating with vendors to request samples and technical documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specification Drafting:&lt;/strong&gt; Assist in translating successful prototypes into formal technical specifications for manufacturing partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Continuous Learning:&lt;/strong&gt; Design and execute experiments under the guidance of senior scientists to analyze data and make technical recommendations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; Bachelor’s degree in Food Science, Chemistry, Microbiology, or a related scientific field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 1–3 years of experience in a lab setting (internship experience in food or beverage development is highly preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Foundation:&lt;/strong&gt; Solid understanding of food chemistry, ingredient functionality, and laboratory safety protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent verbal and written communication skills for reporting experimental findings and collaborating with a tight-knit team.&lt;/li&gt;
