&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are searching for an Electrical Engineer who is excited to work on our hardware product with a cloud-based back-end and help bring new ideas from prototype to production. We’re looking for someone who has worked with PCBA designs that include networking, sensing and interfacing with other hardware components, who is ready to jump in and help continually improve our existing products as well as support the development of the next generation of products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day to Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally to develop reliable, high-quality products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop circuits and PCB designs including power, high-speed digital, RF, and networking circuits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be involved in all steps of the electrical engineering process, from establishing design specifications to product launch, including validation and sustaining efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop requirements, specifications, and validation plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support design compliance with EMI/EMC and applicable regulatory requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate electrical schematics, layout exports, drawings, and BOMs for PCBAs, and manage ECOs in the PLM system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform electrical failure investigations by gathering data and using root cause analysis techniques&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Project Managers to clearly communicate status updates, challenges, and timing impacts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop best practices for reliability and quality of electrical subsystems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the broader product development lifecycle by providing electrical engineering expertise&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS or MS in Electrical Engineering or a similar field with 3+ years of industry experience in product development (consumer/industrial), sustaining, or technology exploration in Robotics, Networking, Sensing, IoT, or related fields&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of best practices for circuit design, including multi-layer PCBs, high-speed signaling, RF, and embedded systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in schematic capture and PCB layout tools (e.g., Altium Designer)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and implementing solutions that integrate electrical and mechanical components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of signal acquisition and analysis tools such as oscilloscopes, DMMs, logic analyzers, data loggers, and spectrum analyzers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience in PCB bring-up, debugging, and validation, including the ability to rework SMT/TH components&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with DFM and DFT as they relate to PCBA design and component selection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with industry standards and compliance (e.g., FCC, CE, UL)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of firmware development (C/C++); PLC programming is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to take initiative and thrive in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented approach to problem solving and knowledge gene

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Electromechanical Sustaining Engineer&lt;/strong&gt; to join our Hardware Sustaining team and serve as its electrical and embedded systems expert. Our connected machines are inherently electromechanical, and the field and production issues we tackle increasingly span the electrical, firmware, and mechanical domains at once. In this role, you&#39;ll lead first-pass electrical and firmware investigations, drive root cause and corrective action on electromechanical failures, and act as the technical bridge between our mechanical, electrical, firmware, and software teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll take sustaining projects from initial analysis through change release – diagnosing problems, scoping the engineering work cleanly, and partnering with the EE and firmware development teams to implement and verify fixes. Success in this role directly improves product quality, reliability, and the customer experience across Bevi&#39;s installed base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day to Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Electromechanical Investigation &amp;amp; Root Cause&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead first-pass electrical, embedded, and firmware investigations of field and production issues across Bevi&#39;s connected hardware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform board- and system-level debug—instrumenting, measuring, and reproducing electromechanical failures such as inter-board communication faults, sensor and actuator behavior, and power or signal integrity issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive robust root cause analysis and corrective action on electromechanical issues, taking projects from initial analysis through containment and change release.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate field symptoms into clearly scoped engineering work packages that the EE and firmware development teams can act on directly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Integration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the sustaining team&#39;s technical bridge across mechanical, electrical, firmware, and software disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the EE and firmware teams to hand off well-defined problems and support implementation and verification of solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the sustaining team in cross-functional design reviews, DFMEA, and PFMEA activities, contributing a credible technical voice in electrical and embedded systems discussions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate and coordinate with manufacturing, quality, and outside vendors and suppliers as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Change Implementation &amp;amp; Documentation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and release ECNs and update BOMs, drawings, and supporting documentation for electromechanical changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and execute test methods to validate fixes and verify compliance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply statistical methods and perform product/process analysis to drive quality improvements, cost reduction, and improved reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support component end-of-life and obsolescence engineering activities for elect

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are searching for an Embedded Engineer who is excited to work on our hardware product with a cloud-based back-end and help bring new ideas from prototype to production. In this role, you will be part of developing and implementing embedded code and android systems code that run our current and future Bevi products. This role will be responsible for advancing the firmware that powers our first to market smart water machine and for developing tools that will enable our engineering team to invent, implement and validate new ways to deliver an exceptional user experience at a rapid pace of development. The Embedded Engineer will work with electrical, hardware, software and other embedded engineers and contribute to overall system definition, documentation and system integration activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day to Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to multi-board firmware architecture that supports reliable operation, remote management, and diagnostics across Bevi&#39;s expanding fleet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement firmware for electromechanical systems, including sensor integration, control algorithms, and low-level hardware-software interaction.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the hardware team on new product bring-up and provide feedback to improve overall machine performance and functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build internal tools that help R&amp;amp;D, product development, and manufacturing monitor, control, and validate systems in development and in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Triage and debug platform and system-level issues on both new and existing products to quickly reduce customer impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to team process improvements such as building out unit test frameworks, build automation and CI/CD, and hardware-in-the-loop and firmware testing capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in code reviews and validation to ensure high-quality releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A BS in Electrical Engineering, Computer Engineering, Computer Science or other related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of hands-on industry experience developing, releasing, and supporting production-quality, reliable firmware.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in embedded C and embedded C++ targeting the ARM Cortex-M family of microcontrollers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with bare-metal and RTOS-based applications controlling electromechanical systems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience across the full product development lifecycle, from initial board bring-up to shipping features and fixes to units in the field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working at the hardware/firmware boundary, including debugging physical systems at the board and system level using tools like oscilloscopes, logic analyzers, and multimeters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of modern software development practices, including version control (e.g. git), build automation, and unit testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with serial communication protocols: UART, I2C, SPI, USB, Ether

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Growth Content Marketing Manager to join our team as part of the paid and organic growth engine of Bevi&#39;s GTM strategy. You will champion Bevi&#39;s paid and organic moat through SEO/AEO, paid content and creative execution, lifecycle email, paid web experience, and emerging owned channels that compound in value over time. Working directly with the Head of Growth Marketing, you will translate brand positioning into high-converting copy, keyword-grounded content, and automated nurture systems that drive measurable pipeline.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role sits at the intersection of strategy and execution. You are equally comfortable building a 12-month paid content and SEO roadmap and personally writing the Instagram caption, TikTok script, and LinkedIn ad copy that turns organic and paid visitors into opportunities. You are the executional creative counterpart to the Head of Growth Marketing on all paid media, turning creative strategy into assets that perform, and you own the paid portion of bevi.co as a conversion surface.&lt;/p&gt;
