&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. SEO/AEO/GEO Strategy and Execution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own Bevi&#39;s SEO and AEO/GEO strategy end-to-end from keyword research, technical audits, and backlink strategy to content briefs with the goal of building a durable organic acquisition channel that compounds quarter over quarter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain a brand-relevant keyword strategy mapped to Bevi&#39;s core verticals, and establish Bevi&#39;s presence in AI-generated search responses (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google SGE) by filling content gaps, structuring for entity recognition and FAQ schema, and treating AEO as a first-class growth channel alongside traditional SEO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with web and data teams to ensure site architecture, page speed, crawlability, and schema markup are optimized; monitor competitor organic share and SERP shifts monthly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Growth Marketing Creative Strategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the end-to-end monthly creative brief process, segmenting by campaign, strategy, audience, value pillars, and asset specs across Meta, TikTok, LinkedIn, and Google and serve as the executional creative lead for all paid media channels, coordinating handoffs to comms, creative, and the agency via Monday.com.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write sharp, persona-specific ad copy across all paid channels and maintain a growing library of vertical-specific copy variants, every asset maps to a value pillar, a target segment, and a specific conversion goal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the monthly creative performance readout and a forward-looking paid content innovation plan -&amp;nbsp; tracking which hooks, formats, and concepts drive the highest CTR and best downstream conversion by channel and vertical, and documenting upcoming creative hypotheses with expected outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3. Content and Website Calendar&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage Bevi&#39;s website content cale

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Bevi is on a mission to transform how beverages are delivered and consumed. Our connected beverage platform eliminates the need for single-use bottles and cans, making it easy, fun, and sustainable to stay hydrated. As the category leader in IoT-enabled beverage technology, we&#39;re building a future where Bevi machines are everywhere people live, work, and connect. We&#39;ve raised over $160M in venture capital, serve thousands of customers across the US, Canada, UK and Ireland, and we&#39;ve been rapidly growing year over year, saving over 1 billion bottles from waste. In addition to driving hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Integration Engineer is the technical owner of Workato (Bevi&#39;s integration platform), all data flows between Bevi&#39;s enterprise systems, EDI connections to retail trading partners, and the master-data layer that keeps customer and account records consistent across NetSuite and Salesforce. Reliable AI agents and analytics depend on this foundation. This role designs and operates the integration fabric that links Salesforce, NetSuite, Shopify, Zendesk, Snowflake, and 15+ other enterprise systems, and designs and implements technical solutions that improve scalability, eliminate cross-system tech-debt, and enables Bevi to build AI agents on top of trustworthy data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on engineering role with platform ownership, architectural authority, and program leadership scope. It is not a recipe-by-recipe ticket-taker role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integration Platform Ownership — Workato/iPaaS (35%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own architecture, design standards, and operational health of the Workato platform&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and build production recipes connecting Salesforce, NetSuite, Shopify, Zendesk, Snowflake, The Well, and other systems in Bevi&#39;s enterprise stack&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish patterns for fault tolerance, error handling, observability, and modular recipe design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage Workato environments (dev, test, prod), release process, and connector inventory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the Workato citizen-builder program: governance, design review, approval, training, and documentation for business-built recipes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-System Architecture &amp;amp; Technical Debt (25%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the cross-system technical-debt reduction program (Q4 priority): scope, measurement, prioritization, and execution across the integration layer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set integration design standards (logging, retry, idempotency, schema management) that apply across the EA team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDI &amp;amp; B2B Connectivity (20%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own EDI vendor evaluation and implementation (current: Staples onboarding, ANSI X12 4010, transaction sets including 810/850/856/214/997)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead vendor selection between EDI-as-a-service platforms (Orderful and similar) and consultant-led builds, including 3-year TCO analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build internal capability for repeatable retail/B2B partner onboarding (Staples first; HB Mason, Amazon, OfficeMax pattern in subsequent waves)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own SFTP infrastructure: server administration, partner onboarding, secure file-transfer service for one-time and recurring data flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-Augmented Engineering &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Partnership (15%)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools (Claude and similar) for diagnosis, recipe design, documentation, and code review&lt;/li&gt;
