&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Strategy &amp;amp; Roadmap&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive the product strategy and roadmap for your hardware initiative, balancing near-term launch milestones with longer-term market opportunity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate customer insights, market signals, and business goals into a clear, defensible product vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make prioritization calls under ambiguity, and bring your team along with you when you do.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the internal champion for your product, aligning stakeholders from engineering to the executive team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer &amp;amp; Market Insight&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get in front of customers, prospects, and channel partners regularly: not just to validate assumptions, but to actively hunt for unmet needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a deep understanding of jobs-to-be-done across the verticals this product will serve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run lightweight experiments to pressure-test hypotheses before committing to full builds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay close to the competitive landscape and surface insights that sharpen our positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
